1. Requirements
---------------

PyViennaCL requires the following build dependencies (given as Debian packages):
 * cmake
 * build-essential -- make, g++, etc..
 * python-dev / python3-dev
 * python-numpy / python3-numpy
 * python-sphinx
 * libboost-python-dev (corresponding to the Python version installed)
 * ocl-icd-opencl-dev (or some other OpenCL SDK)

PyViennaCL supports both Python 2 and Python 3, defaulting to your system's
default Python interpreter version.


2. Installation
---------------

Clone the PyViennaCL git repository and change to that directory:

$> git clone https://github.com/viennacl-dev/pyviennacl.git
$> cd pyviennacl

Then, get the external submodules with

$> git submodule update --init

Next, change to the build directory, configure, make and install:

$> cd build
$> cmake ..
    [ use `cmake -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=path-to-interpreter ..` if needed ]
$> make
$> make install

HTML documentation will be in build/pyviennacl/build/doc, or you can access it
from within the Python interpreter:

>>> import pyviennacl
>>> help(pyviennacl)


3. Authors and Contact
----------------------

PyViennaCL was developed during the 2013 'Google Summer of Code' by 
Toby St Clere Smithe <pyviennacl@tsmithe.net>.

ViennaCL was developed under the aegis of the 'Institute for Microelectronics'
at the 'Vienna University of Technology'.

For any technical questions related to ViennaCL, please use our
mailing list: <viennacl-support@lists.sourceforge.net>


